<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1252,870,933]" pageId="2" pageNumber="421">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,1252,870,897]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="2" pageNumber="421" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,1252,870,897]" pageId="2" pageNumber="421">
Key to genera of 
<taxonomicName box="[365,531,870,896]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Paralecaniini">Paralecaniini</taxonomicName>
(Coccinae) found in the Palaearctic and Oriental Regions
</emphasis>
</heading>
based on adult females, adapted from 
<bibRefCitation author="Hodgson, C. J." box="[576,759,907,933]" pageId="2" pageNumber="421" refId="ref7355" refString="Hodgson, C. J. (1994) The Scale Insect Family Coccidae: An Identification Manual to Genera. CAB International, Wallingford, 639 pp." type="book" year="1994">Hodgson (1994)</bibRefCitation>
